:INFO
Zero-Waste Cleaning Product Brand
Launch a small brand selling concentrated, minimal-packaging cleaning products. Tablet, powder, or concentrated liquid formats in refillable glass or aluminum packaging appeal to sustainability-minded buyers.

:COUNTER.half
$1,500
Minimum viable inventory budget for an Etsy or DTC launch
|
:COUNTER.half
6 Months
Realistic timeline from formulation to first profitable month

:PATH
Formulate the Products
Start with one or two SKUs: an all-purpose cleaner and a dish soap. Source certified organic or naturally-derived surfactants. Test pH, cleaning efficacy, and shelf life before producing inventory.

:PATH
Design the Packaging
Choose packaging that matches your zero-waste message: glass bottles, aluminum tins, or compostable kraft boxes for tablets. Label with ingredients, usage instructions, and a refill or return program.

:PATH
Sell on Etsy and DTC
List on Etsy first for organic discovery. Build a Shopify store for direct sales and better margin. Offer a subscription refill option. Pitch to local zero-waste shops and co-ops for wholesale.

:CHECKLIST
Launch Checklist
[ ] Research cosmetics and cleaning product regulations in your country
[ ] Formulate and stability-test 2 SKUs for 90 days
[ ] Source packaging with less than 5 percent virgin plastic content
[ ] Design labels that meet ingredient disclosure requirements
[ ] Photograph products on a clean, minimal background
[ ] Open an Etsy shop and list with full ingredient transparency
[ ] Build a basic Shopify site for DTC and subscription orders
[ ] Contact 5 local zero-waste stores about wholesale terms

:NOTE
Ingredient transparency is a competitive advantage in zero-waste cleaning. List every ingredient by INCI name on your label and website. Buyers in this category read labels and reward honesty.
